{#-
  _error-shell — centered viewport-min-height layout shell for Error patterns.

  Composed by Error-{404,403,401,500,503,Maintenance,Offline,RateLimited,
  BrowserUnsupported,ComingSoon} (Ring 3 S3.1c) and every future error-like
  page that needs the same centered-viewport layout.

  Composition pattern — Twig {% embed %} with blocks (mirror `_auth-shell`
  verbatim per S3.1 doctrine cascade):

    {% embed '@theme/components/_error-shell/_error-shell.html.twig' with {
      variant: 'default',                  # default | hero
      htmlId: 'error-404',
    } %}
      {% block content %}
        {% include '@theme/components/empty/empty.html.twig' with { ... } %}
      {% endblock %}
    {% endembed %}

  Why {% embed %} and NOT {% include with content: '<...>' %}:
    - Same reasoning as `_auth-shell` (mirror precedent verbatim) — see
      `_auth-shell.html.twig` header §"Why {% embed %}".
    - The shell hosts arbitrary Empty composition + brand-feel inline SVG hero
      + primary + optional secondary CTAs. {% embed %} keeps autoescape ; raw
      string injection bypasses it.

  Variants:
    - default — single-column centered. Empty primitive (Ring 1) with a Lucide
                icon (sm/md size). The canonical error-feel pages
                (404/403/401/500/503/RateLimited/BrowserUnsupported).
    - hero    — single-column centered. Empty primitive (Ring 1) with a custom
                inline SVG illustration (lg size). The brand-feel pages
                (Maintenance/Offline/ComingSoon). Visually softer + warmer.

  Layout: see CSS file header for the box model. Centered both axes.
  min-block-size: 100vh (100dvh on iOS Safari) so the shell fills the
  viewport even when the content is short — mirror `_auth-shell` precedent.

  Parameters:
    htmlId      (string, optional)         — auto-generated; used as DOM id
                                              hook for consumer-level styling.
    variant     (string, optional)         — default | hero (default = default)
    className   (string, optional)         — extra utility classes on <main>

  Blocks (all optional except `content`):
    content      — REQUIRED — typically a {% include %} of the Empty primitive
                   wrapped with the pattern-specific microcopy + icon (default
                   variant) OR custom inline SVG hero (hero variant).
    footer       — optional below the Empty (e.g. "Demander de l'aide" link,
                   "Voir le statut" external link, etc.). Patterns that need a
                   secondary navigation slot use this; terminal token-bound
                   patterns (e.g. Auth-ResetPassword expired) HIDE the footer.

  Accessibility:
    - <main> landmark — the error screen is the page's primary content.
    - The inner Empty primitive (Ring 1) carries the <h1> + region landmark
      (role="region" + aria-labelledby pointing at the h1 id).
    - Per [13-a11y §13 Landmarks] : one <main> per page ; this shell IS the
      page's primary content (errors are full-page).
    - Per [13-a11y §12 Heading hierarchy] : Empty.titleLevel='h1' for page-
      level error pages (lg size + h1).
    - Per [13-a11y §11 Images/icons] : hero SVG inside the content block
      should be aria-hidden=true (Empty's `__illustration` wrapper enforces
      this automatically).
    - Per [13-a11y §17 Cognitive] : every error names the situation + proposes
      an action via the Empty body + actions slots (no dead-ends).
-#}

{%- set htmlId      = htmlId      | default('theme-error-shell-' ~ random()) -%}
{%- set variant     = variant     | default('default') -%}
{%- set className   = className   | default('') -%}

{%- set _classes = ['theme-error-shell'] -%}
{%- if variant == 'hero' -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge(['theme-error-shell--hero']) -%}{%- endif -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

<main class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}" data-variant="{{ variant }}" id="{{ htmlId }}">
  <section class="theme-error-shell__panel">
    {%- block content -%}{%- endblock -%}

    {%- if block('footer') is defined and block('footer') is not empty -%}
      <footer class="theme-error-shell__footer">
        {%- block footer -%}{%- endblock -%}
      </footer>
    {%- endif -%}
  </section>
</main>
